  "body": "<!--NOTE: -->\r\n<!--- General questions should go to the discord chat instead of the issue tracker.-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nDuring Prater genesis our Beacon node could not handle the requested load with event loop lag delays between 30-90 seconds.\r\n\r\nAs a result clock could not keep up. See below genesis was at `15:00:00`, so the clock is about 37 slots late.\r\n```\r\n2021-03-23 15:08:24 [CHAIN]         verbose: Clock slot slot=5\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhat should the node do if this happens? \r\n- Should it try to auto-correct somehow?\r\n- Should it crash and stop the program?\r\n- Should the clock be strictly sequential or allow to jump ahead multiple slots?\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nSome more fun logs from Prater\r\n\r\n```\r\n2021-03-23 15:18:18 [API]              info: Started rest api server address=http://127.0.0.1:9596\r\n2021-03-23 15:18:18 [CHAIN]         verbose: Clock slot slot=89\r\n2021-03-23 15:18:18 [CHAIN]         verbose: Clock slot slot=90\r\n2021-03-23 15:18:18 [CHAIN]         verbose: Clock slot slot=91\r\n```",
